Sorry I didn't post much today. I have a killer line up of tests and 
projects that are taking up most of my time.

Also, is this new bot cloaked from scanners?

::Zardus/DevilDuer::

Zardus enters the bridge, glancing at the scanners and seeing the 
report of a new bot crashing nearby. He activates his comm.

"DevilDuer, a new bot's just nearby. Can you go investigate it?" he 
says into his comm. Without waiting for an answer, he sets off toward 
the room that Wheeljack and Composer were in to check on their 
progress.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
DevilDuer mumbles about being pushed around as he walks out of the 
Alliance base. He looks around the island before diving into the 
water and swimming toward shore.




--- In nbwrpg@y..., "Ralph Ares" <ralph@i...> wrote:
> The air was thick as toast around the landing sight where a ball of 
fire had
> fallen from the sky and scorched the land barren. Cinders still 
hung in the
> air as the flam on a nearby branch crackled like the hands of a 
thousand
> clocks whose voices were stolen by the winds of time. The world 
stood still
> as a mound of ash quivered and opened on all sides to admit a 
solitary
> figure entrance into the world of air and land that was Earth. As 
the figure
> stood, its visibility became less and less opaque until it was 
completely
> invisible, but the last image had it moving just south of the 
setting sun,
> as the golden disk set over the mountains of the land which would 
one day be
> known as Spain.
